CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, page 16, reads: "2. Huge crowds filled every inch of available space in exhibit hall"
TitMainTitle: Group of women, including one wearing light colored hat and dark short sleeve blouse with lace cuffs, holding shopping bag and houndstooth coat, gathered near curved staircase in Syria Mosque for the 1956 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
